    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Paschal's Plantation" case?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Demonstrated the limits of land redistribution efforts</option>
            <option letter="b">Established sharecropping laws</option>
            <option letter="c">Created new labor regulations</option>
            <option letter="d">Protected freedmen's rights</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Paschal's Plantation case showed the limits of land redistribution when freedmen were forced to return land to its former Confederate owner despite Union promises.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Freedmen's Bureau handle labor contracts?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Mediated between planters and freedmen to establish fair contracts</option>
            <option letter="b">Gave all land to freedmen</option>
            <option letter="c">Supported plantation owners exclusively</option>
            <option letter="d">Ignored labor issues entirely</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Freedmen's Bureau mediated between planters and freedmen to establish fair labor contracts, though its effectiveness was limited by insufficient resources.</explanation>
    </question>
