    <question>
        <prompt>What was the impact of the "shop system" in sharecropping?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Created additional debt through overpriced goods</option>
            <option letter="b">Provided fair prices to farmers</option>
            <option letter="c">Improved agricultural efficiency</option>
            <option letter="d">Reduced farming costs</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The shop system forced sharecroppers to buy supplies at inflated prices from plantation stores, creating additional debt and economic dependency.</explanation>
